The paper discusses the application of an evolutionary algorithm for data-driven modelling, which falls under the category of machine learning. The use of genetic programming specifically suggests a focus on evolutionary computation and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of artificial neural networks (ANN) and fuzzy logic, which are also sub-fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence, respectively. This suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the validation of the results through numerical simulations, which suggests a focus on control systems and robotics, falling under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the comparison of the results with classical regression models, which suggests a focus on computational engineering, falling under the sub-category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
